author: Ricky O'Donnell
title: Villanova's Donte Divincenzo can't dunk, but he sure keeps trying
text:
The Wildcats guard is having a rough day.
Villanova entered the NCAA tournament as the No. 1 overall seed. The Wildcats are the defending national champions and were near the top of the polls all season. This team is a powerhouse by any measure, but even great teams can have embarassing moments.
Just ask guard Donte Divincenzo. In the second half against No. 16-seed Mt. Saint Mary’s, Divincenzo botched consecutive dunks attempts:
While that is certainly humiliating, at least he fought for the ball and put it back on his next chance. 
The next one is even worse — or, if you view it from a different lens, better :
We admire your determination, Donte Divincenzo. Keep trying to be great.
